OL,6,FPhilip was told he would be selling
OL,7,Fdrugs for a notorious organised crime
OL,8,Fgang and that from now on he would be
OL,9,Ftheir "property". He said: "Once these
OL,10,Fguys had me in there - they could do
OL,11,Fwhat they wanted . No one could see
OL,12,Fanything or hear anything. They knew I
OL,13,Fhad no connections. I had no one to
OL,14,Fask for help. No one would miss me if
OL,15,FI disappeared."
OL,17,FAs the violence accelerated, Philip
OL,18,Fsays he knew his only chance of
OL,19,Fstaying alive was to go the police.
