OL,4,Cvictims in Greater Manchester
OL,6,FIt was up from 653 referrals the year
OL,7,Fbefore and the highest since
OL,8,Fcomparable records began in 2018.
OL,9,FAcross the UK, some 17,004 potential
OL,10,Fvictims of modern slavery were
OL,11,Freferred to the Home Office in 2023,
OL,12,Fup slightly from 16,921 in 2022. It is
OL,13,Fthe highest annual number since the
OL,14,FNational Referral Mechanism began in
OL,15,F2009.
